The paper deals with local image descriptors and their performance in wide-baseline matching benchmarks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a modification to existing descriptors, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The use of pooling and gradient orientations could also be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions outperforming convolutional neural networks, which suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
